location: Hot Springs Village, Arkansas, United States
postcontent: This handguard was on a new unfired upper I bought. The previous owner who never fired the upper bought this SL version midlength handguard not realizing that this only fits a ROUND front handguard retaining cap. This upper, like most mids, has a TRIANGULAR cap. So he modified and made some cuts in the polymer inside the handguard so it would fit the TRIANGULAR cap. When I got the upper I immediately took them off and put the old school handguards back on. SO this will fit either a ROUND or TRIANGULAR cap but is only designed to fit the ROUND one. Take a look at the pics so you can see the modification the guy made. IF mounted on a midlength upper with ROUND cap you will not be able to see his modification. SO cosmetically the cuts would be under the ROUND cap and not seen. Other than that the Handguard is as NEW. I can't find a mark on it, it's look better than some I've pulled new out of the box.
